               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor and scribe.&#xD;
Groups of lines, alternating with black lines, in the incipit page of Text I and in the incipit of Text II; the beginning of some paragraphs in Text I (s. fols. 1ra, 2ra); the words sälam and Ṣadǝqan (ʾo-Ṣadǝqan) in Text II.&#xD;
Some corrections interlineally and lines marking erasures; elements of the punctuation signs and of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Texts I and II are the same as Texts I and II in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESdsm017">DSM-017</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I:</note>
                     <note>- Text I is the same text as the one included in the Ms. from the church of Baräknaha (Eritrea) and published by C. CONTI ROSSINI in Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea, Asmara 1903, 7-22. However, in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy026">MY-026</ref>a the text is slightly shorter: the final part (from fol. 6ra l.11) which corresponds in the Conti Rossini’s edition pp. 21 l.12-22 l.27 is missing.</note>
                     <note>- Due to the condition of the Ms., the text is in disarray: the incipit is on fol. 9r (first fol. of quire II); after fol. 16vb (last fol. of quire II) it continues on fol. 1r (first fol. of quire I) till fol. 6rb.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II:</note>
                     <note>- Due to the condition of the Ms., the incipit of the text, as well as other passages, is not readable, and the sequence and exact number of the strophes are not known.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus/>Fol. 6ra l.11: ዛ{ቲ፡} መጽሐፍ፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ገ{ድ}ሎሙ፡ ለጻድቃን፨ ዘደብረ፡ ማዕጾ፨ ዘአልቦሙ፡ ኍልቈ፡ በረከተ፡ ፀሎቶሙ፡ ወሐብተ፡ ረድኤቶሙ፡ ለኵሎሙ፡ ጻድቃን፨ ምስሌሆሙ፡ ይደ[sic]ምረነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ አቍባ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለጸሓፊ[፡] &lt;...&gt;<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colophon mentions ʾAqwǝba Mikaʾel, probably the donor, and to the scribe, whose name, however, is not readable. The book is entitled “Gädlä Ṣadǝqan zä-Däbrä Maʿṣo”, “Vita of the Righteous Ones of Däbrä Maʿṣo”. The conclusion in column b is not readable.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
